  "texts": [
    "To better understand the significance of the observed performance differences in the food collection, we analyzed the variations in standard deviations between the models utilizing various tests.",
    "These tests are depicted in Figure 4 as groups corresponding to the models.",
    "The Levene and Brown-Forsythe tests assess the homogeneity of variances between the groups, with the Levene test utilizing the mean and the Brown-Forsythe test employing the median.",
    "Cohen's d quantifies the effect size, indicating the magnitude of the difference between two groups.",
    "Comparison of the total food collected across the three tested models: NetLogo (represented by the orange line), LLM (green line), and Hybrid (blue line)."
  ],
